<div class="container">
    <div class="row">
        <div id="system-information" class="col-md-4 col-md-offset-4">
            <form class="well">
                <h2>System Information</h2>
                <p id="instructions">
                    Please provide data for all of the fields in the System Information form. Safety information
                    will automatically display as data is entered.
                </p>

                <div class="form-group">
                    <label>Battery Type:</label>
                    <select class="form-control" id="battery-type-input">
                        <option value="">Select a type</option>
                        <option value="leadacid">Lead Acid</option>
                        <option value="liioncommercial">Lithium Ion - Commercial (from a reputable manufacturer, NRTL listed or approved by your AHJ)</option>
                        <option value="liionsinglecell">Lithium Ion - Single Cell</option>
                        <option value="liionmulticell">Lithium Ion - Multi Cell</option>
                    </select>
                </div>

                <div class="alert-danger hidden" id="voltage-range-warning" role="alert">
                    Voltage values must be a number between 1 and 999
                </div>

                <div class="form-group">
                    <label>Voltage:</label>
                    <input class="form-control" id="volts-input" type="number" />
                </div>

                <div class="alert-danger hidden" id="scc-range-warning" role="alert">
                    SCC values must be a number between 1 and 500,000
                </div>

                <div class="form-group">
                    <label>
                        Battery Short Circuit Current (Amps) <i class="icon-question-sign help-tooltip" data-title="Determined by the internal resistance and is often given in the battery
manufacturer’s product data."></i>:
                    </label>
                    <input class="form-control" id="amps-input" type="number" />
                </div>

                <div class="alert-danger hidden" id="Duration-range-warning" role="alert">
                    SCC values must be a number between 0.003 and 2
                </div>

                <div class="form-group">
                    <label>Duration of Exposure (Seconds) <i class="icon-question-sign help-tooltip" data-title="Clearing time of upstream fuse or circuit breaker. System Inductance should be taken into account when deriving fuse/breaker clearing time. In addition, when deriving fuse or circuit breaker clearing time the Arcing Current = 0.5 * Short Circuit Current since at the max power point the Arc resistance = System resistance. Enter 2 seconds if you do not know the clearing time."></i>:</label>
                    <input class="form-control" id="duration-input" type="number" />
                </div>

                <div class="form-group">
                    <label>Work Mode:</label>
                    <select class="form-control" id="work-mode-input">
                        <option value="">Select a mode</option>
                        <option value="2" class="lead-acid-work-mode-option">Mode 2 - Testing, troubleshoot, tune and adjust</option>
                        <option value="3" class="lead-acid-work-mode-option">Mode 3 - Energized, Energized Electrical Work Permit (EEWP) to modify, repair or adjust</option>
                        <option value="whilecharging" class="lithium-ion-work-mode-option">While Charging</option>
                    </select>
                </div>



                <div id="form-actions">
                    <hr /><a id="reset-button" href="#" class="btn">Reset</a>
                </div>
            </form>

        </div>
        <div id="results-wrapper" class="col-md-12">
            <div class="section">
                <div id="not-enough-data" class="classification">
                    Please provide data for all of the fields in this form. Safety information
                    will automatically display as valid data is entered.
                </div>
                <div id="class-0" class="classification">Classification <span class="classification-display"></span> - No hazard. No engineering or administrative controls are needed.</div>
                <div id="class-1" class="classification">Classification <span class="classification-display"></span> - Little to no hazards. Few or no engineering or administrative controls are needed.</div>
                <div id="class-2" class="classification">
                    Classification <span class="classification-display"></span> - Injury or death could occur by close proximity or contact;
                    often the hazard is shock or contact burn; engineering controls are necessary for operation (e.g., listing or equipment approval),
                    and administrative controls are necessary for electrical work in this classification.
                </div>
                <div id="class-3" class="classification">
                    Classification <span class="classification-display"></span> - Injury or death could occur by proximity or contact; often the hazard is shock, contact burn,
                    or arc-flash burn; engineering controls are necessary for operation (e.g., listing or equipment approval),
                    and administrative controls are necessary for electrical work in this classification.
                </div>
                <div id="class-4" class="classification">
                    Classification <span class="classification-display"></span> - Highest level of risk. Significant engineering and administrative controls are
                    necessary to manage the hazard in this classification.
                </div>
                <div id="class-5" class="classification">
                    Classification <span class="classification-display"></span> - Highest level of risk. Significant engineering and administrative controls are
                    necessary to manage the hazard in this classification.
                </div>
            </div>

            <div class="section">
                <h3>General</h3>
                <div class="row results">
                    <div class="col-md-4"><div id="watts-display" class="display"></div><h6>Power</h6></div>
                    <div class="col-md-4"><div id="joules-display" class="display"></div><h6>Energy</h6></div>
                </div>
            </div>

            <div class="section">
                <h3>Shock Boundaries</h3>
                <div class="row results">
                    <div class="col-md-4">
                        <div id="limited-approach-fixed-circuit-display" class="display"></div>
                        <h6>
                            Limited Approach Circuit
                            <i id="limited-approach-help" class="icon-question-sign help-tooltip"
                                data-title="Distance from an exposed conductor within which a shock hazard exists. Training or escort required."></i>
                        </h6>
                    </div>
                    <div class="col-md-4">
                        <div id="restricted-approach-display" class="display"></div>
                        <h6>
                            Restricted Approach
                            <i id="restricted-approach-help" class="icon-question-sign help-tooltip"
                                data-title="Distance from an exposed conductor within which there is an increased risk of shock
                    due to electrical arc over combined with inadvertent movement. PPE required."></i>
                        </h6>
                    </div>
                </div>
                <div class="row results">
                    <div class="col-md-4">
                        <div id="prohibited-approach-display" class="display"></div>
                        <h6>
                            Prohibited Approach
                            <i id="prohibited-approach-help" class="icon-question-sign help-tooltip"
                                data-title="Distance from an exposed conductor within which work is considered the same as making contact with the electrical conductor or circuit part."></i>
                        </h6>
                    </div>
                </div>
            </div>

            <div class="section">
                <h3>
                    Arc Flash Boundaries (Applicable at >100V and >500A)<i class="icon-question-sign help-tooltip"
                                                                            data-title="From:
                    <p>Arc Flash Calculations for Exposures to DC Systems - Daniel R. Doan, Senior Member, IEEE - IEEE TRANSACTIONS ON INDUSTRY APPLICATIONS, VOL. 46, NO. 6, NOVEMBER/DECEMBER 2010</p>
                    <p>DC Arc Flash Calculations – Arc-InOpen-Air &amp; Arc-In-A-Box Using a Simplified Approach, Fontaine &amp; Walsh Electrical Safety Workshop (ESW), 2012 IEEE IAS, Date: Jan. 31 2012-Feb. 3 2012</p>"></i>
                </h3>
                <p class="important">The calculated Arc Flash boundary does not account for hearing or lung damage or potential flying debris which may be present during a failure mode event.</p>
                <div class="row results">
                    <div class="col-md-4">
                        <div id="arc-flash-free-space-incident-energy" class="display"></div>
                        <h6>
                            Free Space Incident Energy at 18"
                            <i class="icon-question-sign help-tooltip"
                                data-title="<p>Free space incident energy at a standard working distance of 18&quot;.
                                Assumes worst case of all energy being converted into radiant heat.</p>
                                <p>Calculated from:<br/>
                                Incident Energy = 0.005 * Volts * Current * Time / 46<sup>2</sup><br/>(46cm = 18&quot;)</p>
                                <p>Any questions should be referred to an electrical safety expert.</p>"></i>
                        </h6>
                    </div>
                    <div class="col-md-4">
                        <div id="arc-flash-display-free-space" class="display"></div>
                        <h6>
                            Free Space Arc Flash Boundary for 1.2 cal/cm<sup>2</sup>
                            <i class="icon-question-sign help-tooltip"
                                data-title="<p>Free space threshold distance for 2<sup>nd</sup> degree burn where the worker is exposed to 1.2 cal/cm<sup>2</sup> (5 J/cm<sup>2</sup>)
                                utilizing a multiplying factor of 3 * Free Space. Assumes absolute worst case of all energy being converted into radiant heat.</p>
                                <p>Calculated from:<br/> Distance (cm) = sqrt((0.005 / 1.2) * Volts * Current * Time)</p>
                                <p>PPE is not required when working at or greater than this distance.</p>"></i>
                        </h6>
                    </div>
                </div>
                <div class="row results">
                    <div class="col-md-4">
                        <div id="arc-flash-incident-energy" class="display"></div>
                        <h6>
                            Enclosed Box Incident Energy at 18"
                            <i class="icon-question-sign help-tooltip"
                                data-title="<p>Enclosed Box incident energy at a standard working distance of 18&quot;.
                                Assumes worst case of all energy being converted into radiant heat.</p>
                                <p>Calculated from:<br/>
                                Incident Energy = 3 * 0.005 * Volts * Current * Time / 46<sup>2</sup><br/>(46cm = 18&quot;) </p>
                                <p>A safety factor of 3 * Incident Energy is utilized to account for box energy focusing effects.
                                Any questions should be referred to an electrical safety expert.</p>"></i>
                        </h6>
                    </div>
                    <div class="col-md-4">
                        <div id="arc-flash-display-enclosed-space" class="display"></div>
                        <h6>
                            Enclosed BoxArc Flash Boundary for 1.2 cal/cm<sup>2</sup>
                            <i class="icon-question-sign help-tooltip"
                                data-title="<p>Enclosed Box threshold distance for 2<sup>nd</sup> degree burn where the worker is exposed to 1.2 cal/cm<sup>2</sup> (5 J/cm<sup>2</sup>)
                                utilizing a multiplying factor of 3 * Free Space. Assumes absolute worst case of all energy being converted into radiant heat.</p>
                                <p>Calculated from:<br/> Distance (cm) = sqrt((0.005 / 1.2) * 3 * Volts * Current * Time)</p>
                                <p>PPE is not required when working at or greater than this distance.</p>"></i>
                        </h6>
                    </div>
                </div>
            </div>

            <div class="section">
                <h3>Safety Requirements</h3>
                <p>When working near or on batteries, electrical and physical hazards, as well as chemical and explosive hazards, should be considered. Use additional PPE as required. Contact your AHJ for work control and safety requirements.</p>

                <div class="row results">
                    <div class="col-md-4">
                        <div id="safety-req-workers-display" class="display"></div><h6>
                            Workers <i class="icon-question-sign help-popover"
                                        data-title="Workers Definitions"
                                        data-content="<strong>Alone</strong> - No other workers required.<br/>
                                <strong>Two Person</strong> - An additional worker qualified to work on energized circuits, understanding the work activities and the hazards present, and trained to know what to do in case of an electrical accident involving the other worker. Must be within eyesight of the hazardous task.<br/>
                                <strong>Safety Watch</strong> - The safety watch should be a worker qualified to work on energized circuits who accepts responsibility for monitoring qualified worker(s) performing high-hazard electrical work. Must be actively working with/beside the primary worker and have the same PPE and training."></i>
                        </h6>
                    </div>
                    <div class="col-md-4">
                        <div id="safety-req-work-control-display" class="display"></div><h6>
                            Work Control <i class="icon-question-sign help-popover"
                                            data-title="Training Definitions"
                                            data-content="<strong>EEWP</strong> - Energized Electrical Work Permit, higher level signing authority required<br/>
                                <strong>SOP</strong> - Standard Operating Procedure"></i>
                        </h6>
                    </div>
                </div>
                <div class="row results">
                    <div class="col-md-4"><div id="safety-req-ppe-display" class="display"></div><h6>Required Personal Protective Equipment</h6></div>
                </div>
            </div>

            <div class="section" id="ppe-requirements">
                <h3>Free Space PPE Requirements for Working at a Distance of 18"</h3>
                <p>This analysis is based on 2012 NFPA 70E, Table 130.7(C)(15)(a).</p>
                <div class="row results arc-flash-ppe">
                    <div class="col-md-9">
                        <div id="" class="ppe-display">
                            <h4>Arc Rated Clothing, Minimum Arc rating of <span id="ppe-cal-rating">4</span> cal/cm<sup>2</sup>:</h4>
                            <ul id="ppe-low">
                                <li>Long sleeve shirt and pants, or coveralls</li>
                                <li>Flash suit hood or face shield and balaclava</li>
                                <li>Jacket, parka or rainwear (as needed)</li>
                            </ul>
                            <ul id="ppe-high">
                                <li>Shirt</li>
                                <li>Pants</li>
                                <li>Coveralls</li>
                                <li>Flash suit hood or face shield and balaclava</li>
                                <li>Jacket, parka or rainwear (as needed)</li>
                            </ul>
                        </div>
                    </div>
                </div>
                <div class="row results arc-flash-ppe">
                    <div class="col-md-9">
                        <div id="" class="ppe-display">
                            <h4>Protective Equipment:</h4>
                            <ul>
                                <li>Hard hat</li>
                                <li>safety glasses or goggles</li>
                                <li>hearing protection</li>
                                <li>leather work shoes</li>
                            </ul>
                        </div>
                    </div>
                </div>
                <div class="row results">
                    <div class="col-md-9">
                        <div id="" class="ppe-display">
                            <h4>Minimum Class of Dielectric Gloves with Leather Protectors:</h4>
                            <ul>
                                <li id="glove-class-display">Class 0</li>
                            </ul>
                        </div>
                    </div>
                </div>
            </div>

            <div class="section" id="ppe-requirements-voltage-too-high">
                <h3>Free Space PPE Requirements for Working at a Distance of 18"</h3>
                <div class="row results">
                    <div class="col-md-9">
                        <div class="display">Consult your local AHJ (Authority Having Jurisdiction) for all applicable Safety Requirements.</div>
                    </div>
                </div>
            </div>





            <div class="section" id="enclosed-ppe-requirements">
                <h3>Enclosed Space PPE Requirements for Working at a Distance of 18"</h3>
                <p>This analysis is based on 2012 NFPA 70E, Table 130.7(C)(15)(a).</p>
                <div class="row results enclosed-arc-flash-ppe">
                    <div class="col-md-9">
                        <div id="" class="ppe-display">
                            <h4>Arc Rated Clothing, Minimum Arc rating of <span id="enclosed-ppe-cal-rating">4</span> cal/cm<sup>2</sup>:</h4>
                            <ul id="enclosed-ppe-low">
                                <li>Long sleeve shirt and pants, or coveralls</li>
                                <li>Flash suit hood or face shield and balaclava</li>
                                <li>Jacket, parka or rainwear (as needed)</li>
                            </ul>
                            <ul id="enclosed-ppe-high">
                                <li>Shirt</li>
                                <li>Pants</li>
                                <li>Coveralls</li>
                                <li>Flash suit hood or face shield and balaclava</li>
                                <li>Jacket, parka or rainwear (as needed)</li>
                            </ul>
                        </div>
                    </div>
                </div>
                <div class="row results enclosed-arc-flash-ppe">
                    <div class="col-md-9">
                        <div id="" class="ppe-display">
                            <h4>Protective Equipment:</h4>
                            <ul>
                                <li>Hard hat</li>
                                <li>safety glasses or goggles</li>
                                <li>hearing protection</li>
                                <li>leather work shoes</li>
                            </ul>
                        </div>
                    </div>
                </div>
                <div class="row results">
                    <div class="col-md-9">
                        <div id="" class="ppe-display">
                            <h4>Minimum Class of Dielectric Gloves with Leather Protectors:</h4>
                            <ul>
                                <li id="enclosed-glove-class-display">Class 0</li>
                            </ul>
                        </div>
                    </div>
                </div>
            </div>

            <div class="section" id="enclosed-ppe-requirements-voltage-too-high">
                <h3>Enclosed Space PPE Requirements for Working at a Distance of 18"</h3>
                <div class="row results">
                    <div class="col-md-9">
                        <div class="display">Consult your local AHJ (Authority Having Jurisdiction) for all applicable Safety Requirements.</div>
                    </div>
                </div>
            </div>

            <div class="section">
                <h3>Classes</h3>
                <div class="row results">
                    <div class="col-md-12"><img style="width:100%" src="~/Content/images/battery-classes.png"/></div>
                </div>
            </div>
        </div>
    </div>

